    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Please provide a reproducible, runnable example when reporting an issue (eg include some code that constructs the `info_df`, or a similar dataframe with dummy data that shows the same problem).\r\n\r\nIn case of `info_df.where(info_df[\"info\"]>0.5)`, this introduces missing values (NaN) in dataframe, and this is a limitation of pandas that it cannot represent missing values in integer columns. Therefore your column gets converted to float. See http://pandas.pydata.org/pandas-docs/stable/gotchas.html#nan-integer-na-values-and-na-type-promotions"
  },
